14/10/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- Parliament Speaker Jozefina Topalli visited Paris on Thursday (13 October) to lead a conference on energy and environment in her capacity as chairman of the Parliamentary Assembly of Black Sea Economic Co-operation countries. She presented the new Albanian government's programme, focusing on the war against corruption and organised crime and on efforts to create an efficient and modern administration. 
In Tirana Thursday, Prime Minister Sali Berisha called on local media to join the cabinet's efforts to fight corruption. Berisha stressed that the heads of state institutions should immediately verify any media reports about corruption and launch necessary measures if they prove true. (Albanian News - 14/10/05) 
